                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="pmi-acp-certification-3">
                            <h3>PMI-ACP Certification</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-3">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-1">1. Who provides the PMI-ACP certification? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The PMI-ACP certification is offered by PMI, a world-renowned body dedicated to helping professionals, leaders and organizations learn and validate their knowledge and skills in project management and professional development. <br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-2">2. Can I get PMI-ACP certified without taking the course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You cannot get PMI-ACP certified without undertaking the course as per PMI requirements which includes 21 hours of training by an Authorized Training Partner.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-3">3. What are the prerequisites to take the PMI-ACP certification exam?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>As per the latest <a href="https://www.pmi.org/certifications/agile-acp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PMI guidelines</a>, to qualify for the PMI-ACP exam, you must fulfil the following: </p>
                                            <p><b>PROJECT MANAGEMENT EDUCATION&nbsp;</b></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>21 hours of training in Agile practices from an authorized training partner&nbsp;<br></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><b>PROJECT MANAGEMENT AND AGILE EXPERIENCE&nbsp;</b></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>2,000 hours of general project experience working on teams. While a current PMPÂ® or PgMPÂ® satisfies this requirement, neither certification is mandatory to qualify for the PMI-ACP assessment.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>1,500 hours working on Agile project teams or with Agile methodologies. Please note that this requirement is in addition to the 2,000 hours of general project experience.&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>You can also find these requirements on the <a href="https://www.pmi.org/certifications/agile-acp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PMI page</a>.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-4">4. What is the process to get the PMI-ACP certification? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Here are the four steps to get PMI-ACP certified: &nbsp;</p>
                                            <p><b>Step 1:</b> Validate your eligibility according to <a href="https://www.pmi.org/certifications/agile-acp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PMIâs guidelines</a>.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                            <p><b>Step 2: </b>Take the 21-hour long PMI-ACP course from an Authorized Training Partner of PMI. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                            <p><b>Step 3:</b> Take the PMI-ACP exam and clear it.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
                                            <p><b>Step 4: </b>Become a PMI- Agile Certified Practitioner.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-5">5. Do you provide a course completion certificate?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate on successfully completing the course.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-6">6. How long does it take to get a PMI-ACP certification? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>To obtain the PMI-ACP certification, you would need to attend 21 hours of training under an Authorized Training Partner of PMI. You will also need to clear the PMI-ACP exam and fulfil other conditions of eligibility which you can find on the <a href="https://www.pmi.org/certifications/agile-acp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">PMI page</a>.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-7">7. Will my certificate say âVirtualâ if I take the certification online?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, your certificate will not mention the course was held online. It will look the same as the in-person certificates.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-8">8. Why should I renew my certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>As a result of the engagement and contributions of those who share their ideas and practical experiences in the workplace, Agile practices continue to evolve. PMI requires you to take measures to keep yourself abreast of the latest best practices, tools and techniques in Agile.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
                                            <p>Renewal of your certification validates your Scrum proficiency and demonstrates your interest in the growth and evolution of Scrum.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-3-9">9. How do I renew my PMI-ACP certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-3-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-3">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You would need to renew your PMI-ACP certification every 3 years. You need to earn 30 PDUs during these 3 years to maintain your certification. You can earn these by learning more Agile topics.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
